● The model you should use is:

## `onnx-community/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX`

**Full URL:** https://huggingface.co/onnx-community/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX

This is the ONNX-format conversion of Google's EmbeddingGemma 300M,
  explicitly published by the `onnx-community` org **for use with
  Transformers.js** — which is exactly the library your `chatbot.js` already
  uses.

### Why this one (and not the alternatives)

| Repository | Use it? |
|---|---|
| **`onnx-community/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX`** | ✅ Yes — purpose-built for
  Transformers.js |
| `google/embeddinggemma-300m` | ❌ Raw PyTorch weights — needs conversion |
| `electroglyph/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX-uint8` | ⚠️ Third-party uint8
  variant; only if you want that specific quantization |

### Important caveat when wiring it up

EmbeddingGemma activations **do not support fp16** or its derivatives. You
  must request **fp32** or **q8** quantization when instantiating the
  pipeline, e.g.:

```js
const extractor = await pipeline(
    "feature-extraction",
    "onnx-community/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX",
    { device: "webgpu", dtype: "q8" }   // or "fp32"
);
```

So in `web_assets/chatbot.js:39` you'd change:

```js
const EMBED_MODEL_ID = "Xenova/paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2";
```
to
```js
const EMBED_MODEL_ID = "onnx-community/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX";
```

