The `dtype: "q8"` was **already set** at line 797 — no change needed there.
  WebGPU is preferred with WASM fallback, which is correct.

## Notes

- **Dimension changed 384 → 768.** EmbeddingGemma-300m's native output is
  768-dim (MRL-truncatable to 512/256/128, but I left it at full 768 to keep
  parity with the existing mean-pool + normalize flow).
- **Cache bump required.** Old visitors will have 384-dim vectors cached in
  IndexedDB under the same DB name; the version bump to `2` triggers
  `onupgradeneeded` so the stale store gets rebuilt. First load after this
  change will re-download the new model (~300 MB) and re-index chunks.
- **No build step needed** — the embedding happens entirely browser-side;
  `scripts/build_chatbot_index.py` only produces text chunks and doesn't
  reference the model.

A heads-up worth flagging: EmbeddingGemma uses its own prompt template
  prefix (e.g. `title: none` / `task: search result`) for best retrieval
  quality, but transformers.js's `feature-extraction` pipeline applies the
  tokenizer's default handling. The plain `pooling: "mean", normalize: true`
  call you already use will work functionally; you may get slightly better
  retrieval by prefixing queries with the model's recommended instruction,
  but that's an optimization, not a correctness issue.

