● Good catch — that's a WebGPU error, and it's coming from my embedding model
  change. Here's what's happening:

EmbeddingGemma is built on the **Gemma architecture**, and transformers.js's
  WebGPU execution provider can't compile some of its ops into a shader
  pipeline (`getBindGroupLayout` is a WebGPU API — the failure happens
  during pipeline creation). The old MiniLM was a BERT-style model that ran
  fine on WebGPU; EmbeddingGemma (Gemma-based) doesn't.

The fix: run the embedder on **WASM** instead of WebGPU. A 300M embedding
  model on WASM is fast enough (embeddings are computed once per query, not
  token-by-token generation), and it avoids the WebGPU device entirely so
  there's no conflict with the Gemma chat model.

